The paper proposes a deep learning model for Online Handwritten Chinese Character Recognition (OLHCCR) using stroke sequence information and eight-directional features. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. The use of deep learning also suggests that it could belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper involves recognition tasks, which could suggest that it belongs to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
